                  </persName>
            . I am the wife of John Ord. The prisoner's daughter learned work of me; I have pawned things for the prisoner, and have lent her things to pawn, but I never had any of the money; I never allowed her to take things without my lending them to her - I did not allow her to take this bed; she had taken my fire-irons and other things.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. My husband has been away two years and five months; when I took the bed, and got the monthly note, I had to wait till half-past seven o'clock before I got the money for it.</p>
